    "Related Work": "The proposed idea builds upon existing frameworks like Spectral Latent Steering and Spectral Quantization Routing, which utilize spectral properties for optimization. However, unlike these works that focus on static projections or precision routing, Adaptive Spectral Dilation actively modifies the shape of the activation space in real time based on diagnostics such as curvature and condition number, allowing for a more dynamic response to distribution shifts.",
    "Abstract": "In this work, we propose Adaptive Spectral Dilation, a novel framework that enhances model stability and inference efficiency by dynamically manipulating the geometric properties of activation spaces during runtime. By utilizing curvature-aware diagnostics of activation geometry, we compute dilation factors that adjust the scale of activations based on their condition number and spectral decay rate. This adaptive mechanism allows for real-time adjustments to the activation landscape, ensuring that the model remains robust to perturbations and distributional shifts without the need for retraining. We will empirically validate the effectiveness of this approach on standard benchmarks, demonstrating significant improvements in both throughput and accuracy compared to existing static methods. The proposed framework not only bridges theoretical insights from spectral geometry with practical implications for ML deployment but also sets a new direction for training-free adaptive mechanisms.",
