**IDEA JSON:**
```json
{
  "idea": {
    "Name": "curvature_aware_training_free_models",
    "Title": "Curvature-Aware Training-Free Framework for Enhanced Robustness in Machine Learning Models",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Can we utilize curvature-aware geometric principles to enhance the robustness and performance of training-free machine learning models?",
    "Related Work": "Existing training-free models such as NEAR and Coefficients Learning focus on reducing training overhead. However, they often overlook the geometric considerations of representation spaces, which can lead to suboptimal robustness. This proposal distinguishes itself by explicitly integrating curvature diagnostics into the training-free paradigm, leveraging mathematical precision to enhance model stability.",
    "Abstract": "This research aims to explore the integration of curvature-aware representation geometry within training-free machine learning frameworks to enhance model robustness and performance. While training-free methods reduce computational overhead, they often neglect the geometric properties of representation spaces, which can lead to fragility in model performance. Our approach utilizes curvature diagnostics to inform adaptive routing protocols, enabling models to maintain stability under varying conditions. We will empirically validate the framework through a series of experiments that assess the robustness of curvature-aware training-free models against traditional methods, focusing on metrics such as gradient covariance decay and Hessian conditioning. This work will contribute to the theoretical understanding of the interplay between geometry and training-free methodologies, providing a pathway for future explorations in efficient machine learning.",
    "Experiments": [
      "1. Implement a baseline training-free model without curvature awareness and a curvature-aware model.",
      "2. Evaluate both models on synthetic datasets with varying degrees of noise to assess stability and performance.",
