    "Related Work": "While existing literature focuses on training-based optimization and adaptive routing strategies, there is a notable gap in exploring curvature-aware methods that function without training. Most studies emphasize heuristic approaches to routing and representation learning, but few investigate deterministic mechanisms grounded in curvature diagnostics. This proposal distinguishes itself by offering a mathematically rigorous, training-free alternative that integrates spectral analysis and geometric insights.",
    "Abstract": "Recent advancements in adaptive routing have primarily relied on training-based methods, presenting challenges in robustness and generalization. This proposal introduces a novel curvature-aware adaptive routing framework that operates without training, leveraging geometric diagnostics to optimize representation learning in neural networks. By employing a deterministic approach grounded in curvature analysis, we aim to establish a principled method for dynamically adjusting routing paths based on the local geometry of the loss landscape. Our framework will utilize projection-based mechanistic probes to quantify gradient covariance decay and Hessian conditioning, enabling real-time diagnostics that inform routing decisions. We will validate our approach through a series of empirical experiments, comparing performance metrics such as generalization error and computational efficiency against traditional training-based methods. This research aims to provide a rigorous foundation for the development of training-free adaptive routing protocols that enhance the stability and reliability of machine learning models, ultimately contributing to the theoretical understanding of representation learning.",
    "Experiments": [
