    "Related Work": "Existing work such as HOBBIT and KVTuner has focused on mixed-precision strategies but often overlook dynamic environmental factors affecting latency. This proposal distinguishes itself by integrating real-time feedback mechanisms into the quantization process, ensuring that the system can adaptively respond to changes in workload and latency requirements.",
    "Abstract": "In the realm of machine learning inference, particularly with large language models and vision transformers, optimizing latency while maintaining accuracy is a persistent challenge. Current mixed-precision quantization techniques fail to incorporate real-time latency monitoring, which can lead to suboptimal performance under varying computational loads. We propose an Adaptive Latency-Aware Mixed-Precision Quantization framework that utilizes a feedback loop to continuously adjust the precision of model layers based on real-time latency and workload metrics. This framework aims to enhance inference efficiency, especially in edge environments where resource constraints are critical. Our approach will be validated through extensive experiments, focusing on throughput-accuracy trade-offs and measuring latency impacts across different models and hardware setups. The anticipated outcomes include a substantial improvement in inference speed without compromising model accuracy, making this framework suitable for practical deployment scenarios.",
