Based on the literature search, I have identified relevant works that inform the novelty and direction of the proposed research idea. Notably, the works on latency-aware designs and efficient ML inference serving frameworks highlight the growing importance of optimizing model performance while adhering to strict latency constraints. However, none of the identified studies explicitly connect the PAC-Bayes frameworks with Jacobian-based layer-skipping techniques in the context of inference latency and strictly bounded overhead protocols, which remains an underexplored area.

I propose refining the initial idea to focus on a specific gap observed in the literature regarding the integration of PAC-Bayes principles with a Jacobian-based layer-skipping framework. This refined proposal aims to develop a novel method for optimizing inference efficiency while ensuring strict latency guarantees, distinguishing it from existing works.

Here’s the refined proposal:

