rovides a mathematically grounded pathway for resource allocation under dynamic input distributions, contributing to the growing field of training-free optimization in machine learning.', 'Experiments': ['1. Evaluate the effectiveness of SGR on standard benchmarks, comparing throughput and accuracy against static mixed-precision methods.', '2. Measure the latency impact of dynamic precision adjustments by analyzing wall-clock time across varying computational loads.', '3. Conduct an ablation study to isolate contributions of local covariance diagnostics and spectral decay metrics on precision routing decisions.', "4. Assess robustness against adversarial inputs by benchmarking SGR's performance on perturbed datasets."], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Potential computational overhead associated with real-time diagnostics, although minimized through efficient SVD implementations.', 'The effectiveness of dynamic routing may vary with the complexity of the model architecture and input distributions.', 'Initial implementation may require fine-tuning of thresholds for covariance and spectral metrics to achieve optimal performance.']}
