    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a novel framework for Dynamic Curvature Adaptation (DCA) that leverages curvature properties of the loss landscape to enhance training-free optimization processes in machine learning models. Unlike existing methods that require retraining or static optimization paths, DCA adapts to the changing characteristics of input data by employing real-time curvature diagnostics derived from activation covariances. By integrating these curvature metrics, we hypothesize that the optimization process can be significantly improved, resulting in enhanced model performance and stability under distributional shifts. The proposed approach will be evaluated through empirical tests on standard ML benchmarks, focusing on metrics such as accuracy, computational efficiency, and stability. By incorporating curvature-aware insights directly into the optimization routine, DCA will provide a transparent, mathematically grounded framework for achieving robust performance in dynamic environments.",
