    "Title": "Dynamic Spectral Precision Routing: A Training-Free Framework for Adaptive Numerical Precision in Machine Learning",
    "Short Hypothesis": "We hypothesize that by leveraging local spectral properties of activation spaces, we can develop a training-free adaptive precision routing mechanism that dynamically allocates numerical precision based on the spectral condition of input features, improving inference speed and resource efficiency without compromising accuracy.",
    "Related Work": "Existing works such as Spectral Latent Steering and Spectral Quantization Routing have explored adaptive mechanisms for optimization and precision allocation, but they either rely heavily on heuristic methods or static profiling. This proposal distinguishes itself by offering a fully training-free mechanism that uses real-time spectral diagnostics to inform precision allocation, eliminating the need for costly calibration and enhancing transparency.",
    "Abstract": "In modern machine learning, the trade-off between inference speed and numerical precision is often managed through heuristic approaches, which can lead to suboptimal performance and opaque decision-making processes. This proposal introduces a novel framework for Dynamic Spectral Precision Routing (DSPR), which leverages real-time spectral analysis of activation spaces to inform adaptive numerical precision allocation during inference. By employing randomized singular value decomposition to assess the local covariance and condition number of hidden states, our method enables precise routing of computational resources based on the geometric properties of the input data. This training-free approach eliminates the overhead of traditional training methods while maintaining high accuracy and efficiency. Our empirical evaluations on single-GPU setups across diverse benchmarks will demonstrate the effectiveness of DSPR in achieving a superior throughput-accuracy Pareto frontier compared to existing static and heuristic baselines. This work not only advances the understanding of spectral conditioning in machine learning but also provides a scalable, transparent framework for adaptive resource allocation in real-time applications.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Evaluate the effectiveness of DSPR against static precision allocation baselines on standard machine learning benchmarks.",
      "Measure the dynamic adaptation of numerical precision based on spectral diagnostics in real-time settings using various input distributions.",
      "Conduct ablation studies to quantify the contribution of spectral condition number and covariance metrics to overall system performance.",
      "Utilize metrics such as throughput, accuracy, and computational efficiency to assess performance improvements."
