    "Title": "Training-Free Adaptive Routing and Curvature-Aware Quantization Diagnostics",
    "Short Hypothesis": "A training-free adaptive routing framework can be enhanced by integrating curvature-aware quantization diagnostics to optimize mixed-precision quantization strategies while ensuring theoretical performance guarantees.",
    "Related Work": "While recent works like EMQ and SNIP have explored training-free and adaptive quantization techniques, they lack a rigorous mathematical framework that connects the curvature properties of models to the performance of quantization strategies. Our approach emphasizes the theoretical foundations of curvature-aware optimization, providing a novel lens through which to evaluate and improve quantization methods.",
    "Abstract": "In the quest for efficient machine learning models, mixed-precision quantization has emerged as a key strategy for reducing computational overhead while maintaining model accuracy. Existing training-free approaches, such as EMQ and SNIP, have made significant advances in optimizing quantization parameters. However, they often overlook the importance of a solid theoretical foundation to understand the underlying performance dynamics. This research proposes a novel framework that integrates training-free adaptive routing with curvature-aware quantization diagnostics. By employing geometric diagnostics and mathematical transparency, we aim to establish a link between model curvature and quantization efficiency. Our approach will allow us to optimize quantization strategies while ensuring rigorous theoretical performance guarantees, potentially leading to significant advancements in model efficiency without compromising accuracy. We will validate our framework through a series of empirical experiments on standard benchmark datasets, focusing on its ability to improve both computational efficiency and model robustness.",
