    "Related Work": "While several existing frameworks such as InfoQ and EMQ focus on layer-wise quantization strategies and training-free methods, they predominantly assess local metrics for quantization without exploring the global consequences of these decisions. This proposal distinctly innovates by introducing a framework that evaluates global sensitivity to quantization errors, providing a comprehensive approach to mixed-precision quantization.",
    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a Training-Free Global Sensitivity Analysis Framework for Mixed-Precision Quantization, addressing the critical need for effective quantization strategies in deep neural networks. Current methods typically rely on local metrics and extensive training, often leading to suboptimal performance. Our framework leverages a single forward pass to assess the global impact of quantization on model performance, introducing a novel global sensitivity score that quantifies the cascading effects of layer-wise quantization errors. By systematically evaluating how each layer's quantization influences the overall model, we aim to optimize bit-width allocations without retraining. This approach not only simplifies the quantization process but also enhances model robustness and efficiency. Extensive experiments will validate our framework across various networks and datasets, demonstrating significant improvements in inference efficiency while maintaining competitive accuracy.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Conduct experiments on popular architectures (e.g., ResNet, MobileNet) to evaluate the proposed sensitivity-based quantization method versus state-of-the-art approaches.",
