    "Related Work": "Existing approaches like EMQ and TAQ focus on heuristic-based or task-specific quantization without a formal geometric foundation. This proposal distinguishes itself by employing curvature-aware precision routing based on deterministic spectral estimators, which has not been extensively explored in the context of mixed-precision quantization.",
    "Abstract": "In the realm of mixed-precision quantization, existing methodologies often rely on heuristic approaches or task-specific calibration, leading to suboptimal performance and inefficiencies. This proposal introduces a novel geometry-aware framework for adaptive mixed precision quantization that leverages curvature diagnostics and deterministic spectral estimators to optimize precision allocation dynamically. By formulating the quantization process as a geometric optimization problem, we can derive explicit mathematical formulations that ensure both efficiency and accuracy in model deployment. Our framework prioritizes training-free methods, thus eliminating costly training cycles and enhancing deployment feasibility. The effectiveness of our approach will be validated through empirical studies on standard benchmarks, demonstrating its superiority over existing methods in both accuracy and computational efficiency.",
