    "Related Work": "While existing works like 'KVTuner' and 'DQMQ' focus on sensitivity-aware and data quality-aware mixed-precision approaches, they do not explicitly incorporate real-time latency constraints into their quantization strategies. This proposal uniquely combines adaptive quantization with latency-awareness, differentiating it from prior models that primarily target static performance metrics.",
    "Abstract": "In this proposal, we introduce an innovative adaptive mixed-precision quantization framework that explicitly incorporates latency constraints during inference for machine learning models. Unlike existing methods that focus solely on accuracy or memory efficiency, our approach dynamically adjusts the precision of model parameters based on real-time latency feedback. By employing a hybrid reinforcement learning strategy, we learn optimal quantization strategies that respond to varying computational environments and performance requirements, thus ensuring efficient resource utilization. Our framework allows for a tiered deployment of mixed-precision models, where critical layers can operate at higher precision to maintain accuracy while less critical layers can be down-quantized to enhance overall throughput. We will validate our framework through extensive experiments across various model architectures and datasets, measuring both latency and accuracy to establish a Pareto frontier for efficient inference. This work aims to set a new standard for latency-aware ML deployments in edge computing scenarios.",
    "Experiments": [
