    "Title": "Harnessing Tropical Geometry for Training-Free Adaptive Routing in Machine Learning",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Utilizing tropical geometry can enhance training-free representation methods, leading to more robust and interpretable adaptive routing strategies in machine learning without the need for extensive training datasets.",
    "Related Work": "Previous works have explored tropical geometry in neural networks and probabilistic models, but none have focused on employing tropical geometric principles for training-free adaptive routing systems. This proposal distinctly seeks to operationalize tropical geometry for deterministic routing, presenting a new application not covered in existing literature.",
    "Abstract": "This proposal aims to investigate the potential of tropical geometry in developing training-free adaptive routing mechanisms for machine learning models. By leveraging the principles of tropical algebra, we will explore a deterministic framework that allows for effective representation and routing of data without the requirement of extensive training. The objective is to establish a method that combines the geometric insights gained from tropical representations with rigorous linear algebra techniques to formulate a novel adaptive routing protocol. We will evaluate the performance of this method against traditional training-based approaches, focusing on metrics such as accuracy, interpretability, and computational efficiency. This work promises to contribute to the advancement of machine learning models that are not only efficient but also provide transparency in their decision-making processes.",
    "Experiments": [
