Based on the literature search results, I can see that adaptive mixed-precision quantization is a well-explored area with several recent contributions, such as the EMQ framework and the AMP-ViT approach. However, the existing work largely focuses on training-based or post-training quantization techniques and their hardware implementations, often requiring significant computational resources for optimization and evaluation.

To differentiate my proposal and provide a novel angle, I propose a unique adaptive quantization strategy that leverages a lightweight, training-free proxy model to dynamically adjust quantization levels based on real-time performance metrics during inference, instead of relying on pre-trained parameters or extensive training processes.

