    "Short Hypothesis": "Can a training-free, lightweight proxy model dynamically adjust mixed precision quantization during inference based on real-time performance metrics, leading to improved efficiency and accuracy in machine learning models?",
    "Related Work": "While existing approaches in adaptive mixed precision focus on training-based optimizations or hardware adaptations, this proposal introduces a novel training-free framework that dynamically adjusts quantization levels in real-time based on performance metrics, providing an innovative approach to mixed precision quantization without heavy pre-training costs.",
    "Abstract": "In the realm of machine learning, mixed precision quantization has emerged as a powerful technique to enhance efficiency, particularly for edge devices. However, existing methods predominantly rely on extensive training or fixed post-training strategies, limiting their adaptability to varying inference conditions. This proposal introduces an innovative adaptive inference quantization framework that leverages a lightweight training-free proxy model, enabling dynamic adjustments of mixed precision levels based on real-time performance metrics such as latency and accuracy during inference. By integrating this approach, we aim to maintain optimal performance while minimizing resource consumption. Experimental evaluations will focus on various benchmarks to validate the framework's effectiveness in achieving a favorable throughput-accuracy trade-off compared to static quantization methods, ultimately contributing to more efficient machine learning deployments in resource-constrained environments.",
    "Experiments": [
      "1. Implement a lightweight proxy model that estimates the optimal quantization levels based on real-time latency and accuracy metrics during inference.",
