    "Risk Factors and Limitations": "The main risks include the potential for increased complexity in the model and the challenge of accurately measuring the contributions of samples in real-time. Additionally, there may be limitations in the generalizability of results across different datasets, as the proposed adaptive strategies may perform variably based on data characteristics."
  }
}
```

