y to optimize LLM performance in constrained environments.', 'Experiments': ['1. Implement the PCA-based activation projection in an existing LLM architecture, applying it during the inference phase to separate signals.', "2. Conduct controlled experiments on multiple ICL benchmarks, introducing distributional shifts to evaluate the model's robustness and accuracy retention.", '3. Compare performance metrics, including accuracy, inference time, and resource allocation, against baseline models without geometric filtering.', '4. Analyze the stability of subspace alignment post-projection using variance thresholds and assess the impact on model performance.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['The approach may not generalize well to all types of distributional shifts.', 'Computational overhead from PCA computation during inference could introduce latency.', 'The effectiveness of geometric filtering may vary based on the model architecture and specific tasks.']}
