    "Related Work": "Current literature emphasizes optimization-driven ML frameworks but typically relies on extensive training data or complex iterative processes. This proposal distinguishes itself by focusing on training-free representation geometry and its impact on optimization, which is less explored in existing work. While methods exist for optimizing ML models in dynamic environments, they often overlook the geometric properties of the representation space and the implications for adaptive routing.",
    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a novel curvature-aware adaptive routing framework aimed at optimizing representation geometry in machine learning models without the need for extensive training datasets. By leveraging curvature diagnostics, we aim to establish a deterministic routing protocol that optimally navigates the representation space, enhancing numerical stability and efficiency. The proposed method will be validated through a series of empirical experiments demonstrating its efficacy in various machine learning tasks, including classification and regression. We will employ rigorous evaluation metrics to assess performance improvements over conventional training-dependent approaches, thereby contributing to the understanding of training-free optimization strategies in machine learning.",
    "Experiments": [
