    "Related Work": "Existing works primarily focus on layer-wise optimization and often struggle to capture the inter-layer dependencies that govern the overall network performance. For example, while EMQ and InfoQ provide frameworks for training-free quantization, they do not explicitly account for how the quantization of one layer affects subsequent layers. This proposal distinguishes itself by explicitly modeling these dependencies through a new metric that quantifies the influence of each layer's quantization on the entire network's sensitivity.",
