    "Abstract": "This proposal introduces a novel approach to mixed-precision quantization by integrating adaptive pruning strategies, aiming to optimize model performance while reducing computational overhead. Existing training-free quantization methods often overlook the role of parameter importance, leading to suboptimal results in low-bit configurations. We propose a framework that identifies and retains critical parameters through a deterministic pruning strategy, allowing more effective quantization of less important parameters. By leveraging curvature-aware diagnostics and gradient covariance metrics, we can create a robust pipeline that enhances the correlation between quantization proxies and accuracy. Our approach will be empirically validated on standard benchmarks, showcasing its effectiveness in maintaining model integrity while reducing resource usage. This research not only aims to contribute to the quantization domain but also seeks to provide a theoretical underpinning for adaptive pruning in mixed-precision contexts.",
