    "Short Hypothesis": "Dynamic adjustments of kernel parameters during inference, based on real-time profiling data, can lead to significant improvements in latency and throughput over static optimizations.",
    "Related Work": "Existing work on operator fusion and CUDA optimizations typically focuses on static performance enhancements or theoretical frameworks. This proposal introduces a real-time feedback mechanism to dynamically tune kernel parameters, leveraging actual hardware performance metrics to adapt to workload variations.",
    "Abstract": "In this proposal, we introduce the Kernel Performance Tuner (KPT), a novel system designed to optimize machine learning inference through dynamic adjustments of kernel execution parameters. Unlike traditional approaches that rely on static optimizations, KPT leverages real-time profiling data to adaptively tune kernel configurations—such as tile sizes, data layouts, and precision—during inference. By establishing a continuous feedback loop that monitors hardware performance metrics, KPT can exploit transient states and workload variations, potentially yielding superior performance in terms of latency and throughput. Our approach emphasizes empirical evaluation on commodity GPUs, utilizing rigorous profiling techniques to validate improvements. We anticipate that KPT will demonstrate significant end-to-end speedups over existing static methods, providing a new direction for real-time optimization in machine learning inference systems.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Implement KPT in a CUDA-based inference engine and evaluate its performance on standard ML models like ResNet-50 and BERT.",
      "Conduct A/B testing comparing KPT's dynamic tuning against static optimized kernels, measuring p50/p99 latency and throughput under varying batch sizes.",
      "Profile and analyze kernel performance metrics, including occupancy, memory bandwidth utilization, and arithmetic intensity, to attribute performance gains to specific kernel adjustments."
    ],
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": "Potential risks include the overhead of real-time profiling impacting performance gains, and the challenge of tuning multiple parameters simultaneously. Limitations may arise from hardware constraints or model architecture compatibilities that restrict the range of feasible optimizations."
  }
}
```

This proposal aligns with my methodological preferences, focusing on empirical measurements and real hardware performance, while also presenting a clear, innovative approach to optimizing machine learning inference.
