ificant speedups over existing state-of-the-art quantization methods while maintaining model accuracy.', 'Experiments': ['Kernel Profiling: Measure wall-clock latency and throughput for various configurations of mixed precision on commodity GPUs.', 'Quantization Strategy Testing: Implement KBHQ on a set of standard models (e.g., ResNet, ViT) and compare against traditional mixed-precision methods.', "Dynamic Adjustment Evaluation: Test the adaptive mechanism's performance by varying load conditions and assessing the adjustments in precision and kernel execution.", 'Performance Metrics: Evaluate p50/p99 latency, throughput under batching, and energy per token across different configurations.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': 'Potential risks include limited generalizability across different GPU architectures and potential overhead associated with real-time profiling. Furthermore, the performance of the hybrid approach may be sensitive to the specific models being tested, and extensive validation across a wide range of architectures may be necessary.'}
