### Reflection on the Proposal

The initial idea centered on exploring the trade-offs between quantization levels and model accuracy through an information-theoretic lens. However, the literature reveals a growing body of work in mixed-precision quantization and lossy source coding, indicating that while the area is rich, the exploration of fundamental trade-offs under specific rate-distortion constraints remains underexplored.

The existing works, such as QARV and SNIP, focus on adaptive quantization strategies and mixed-precision frameworks, but they often lack a thorough theoretical underpinning that connects the quantization choices to information-theoretic limits. My proposal will thus aim to fill this gap by providing a structured framework that links quantization directly to achievable rates and distortion measures grounded in information theory.

### Refined Proposal

Here’s the refined proposal that maintains the essence of the original idea but emphasizes clarity, novelty, and feasibility.

