Given this context, I propose a novel research idea that builds on the theoretical foundations of rate-distortion principles while introducing a new perspective on model compression through the lens of mutual information maximization. This proposal will differentiate itself by focusing on the joint optimization of quantization and pruning, ensuring task-relevant information is preserved while quantifying the trade-offs involved in a principled manner.

Here’s the refined proposal:

