    "Related Work": "Existing literature has primarily focused on either quantization or pruning independently, or has applied heuristic methods without a strong theoretical foundation. Notably, works such as 'Rate Distortion For Model Compression' provide valuable insights but often do not connect quantization and pruning in a joint optimization framework. Our proposal distinguishes itself by integrating these components through mutual information, allowing for a comprehensive understanding of task-relevant information preservation.",
    "Abstract": "In this paper, we propose a novel framework for neural network compression that jointly optimizes quantization and pruning by maximizing mutual information between the original network's outputs and those of the compressed network. We establish a theoretical foundation based on rate-distortion principles, demonstrating that preserving task-relevant information can be formulated as a mutual information maximization problem subject to a bit rate constraint. Our approach will provide an operational bound on the achievable compression rate while ensuring minimal distortion in predictive performance. We will validate our framework through empirical experiments on benchmark datasets, measuring compression efficiency and accuracy against leading state-of-the-art methods.",
    "Experiments": [
