Based on the literature search results, it is clear that there is a strong emphasis on optimizing inference for large language models (LLMs) through various quantization and kernel optimization strategies. However, many of these works focus on high-level abstractions or training-based methods that do not align with the hardware-first, empirical approach of profiling and kernel-level optimizations that I advocate for. This suggests an opportunity to explore a novel proposal that directly addresses kernel efficiency through empirical performance tuning without relying on theoretical frameworks.

**Refined Proposal:**

