    "Related Work": "Existing literature, such as Astra and KRISP, utilizes automated systems and LLMs for kernel optimization but often lacks rigorous profiling integration that measures specific hardware interactions. This proposal distinguishes itself by prioritizing detailed profiling to inform kernel optimization decisions, ensuring that performance gains are grounded in empirical evidence.",
    "Abstract": "In the quest for efficient GPU inference, this proposal introduces a novel profiling-aided kernel optimization framework that emphasizes empirical measurement over heuristic methods. Unlike existing automated optimization systems that rely on LLMs or generic heuristics, our approach systematically identifies and targets performance bottlenecks using real-time profiling data. By instrumenting kernels to capture detailed metrics such as occupancy, memory access patterns, and arithmetic intensity, we can derive actionable insights that directly inform kernel modifications. The proposed framework will conduct a series of experiments to validate its effectiveness against baseline kernels, demonstrating significant latency reductions and throughput improvements. This work aims to bridge the gap between theoretical optimization strategies and practical, hardware-aware implementations, providing a reproducible and transparent pathway to enhanced GPU performance.",
