### Proposal Refinement

The proposed research idea is to explore a novel method for optimizing inference latency in deep learning models through a hardware-aware scheduling mechanism that dynamically allocates compute resources based on real-time profiling metrics. This approach will focus on minimizing wall-clock latency and maximizing throughput by leveraging kernel-level optimizations while ensuring reproducibility and empirical validation.

### Revised Proposal

IDEA JSON:
