### Proposal Reflection and Refinement

The initial idea proposed previously can be refined by integrating insights from the literature while distinctly positioning it as a novel approach to optimize GPU inference through a systematic analysis of kernel-level throughput, focusing on empirical profiling and specific hardware interactions.

#### Novel Contribution
The refined proposal will specifically target the optimization of tensor-core utilization on commodity GPUs through a novel kernel fusion technique that dynamically adjusts tile sizes based on real-time occupancy metrics. This contrasts with existing methods that often apply static optimizations or rely on general heuristics without real-time profiling feedback.

### Finalized Proposal

