### Reflection
This proposal is novel as it focuses specifically on runtime adaptations of kernel execution, which has not been extensively explored in the existing literature. It is feasible within an academic lab setting as it builds upon existing CUDA frameworks and profiling tools. The experiments can be conducted with available resources and are designed to yield clear, quantifiable results that align with performance metrics crucial for practical deployment in machine learning systems.
