This presents an opportunity to propose a novel research idea that systematically investigates the relationship between model compressibility and task-specific performance while articulating the fundamental limits of such compressibility.

### Proposal Refinement

**Research Idea:**
I propose a framework that seeks to characterize and optimize the trade-off between model compressibility and predictive performance, grounded in information-theoretic principles. This framework will utilize rate-distortion theory to derive achievable rates for different model architectures under varying distortion measures linked to task performance. 

