 and the demands of modern LLMs, offering practical solutions that can be implemented in existing GPU infrastructures.","Experiments":"1. Implement a baseline KV cache management system for LLM inference. 2. Develop an adaptive KV cache optimization algorithm that utilizes real-time profiling data to adjust the cache layout and eviction policy. 3. Conduct A/B testing on hardware to compare the performance of the adaptive system against the baseline. 4. Measure and report p50/p99 latency, tokens-per-second, and memory bandwidth utilization. 5. Analyze the impact of various cache configurations on inference speed and memory efficiency using a range of LLMs.","Risk Factors and Limitations":"1. The adaptation mechanism may introduce overhead that could negate latency gains. 2. Performance may vary significantly across different models and batch sizes. 3. The method is contingent on accurate profiling, and any inaccuracies could lead to suboptimal cache management. 4. The complexity of implementing dynamic cache management may pose challenges in practical deployment."}}
